CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 30, 1949, pg. 4, reads: "Religious Services for the late Charlie Williams were conducted at Ebenezer Church, Monday, with the Rev. Robert Johnson officiating... Top right: Hundreds of friends, unable to gain entrance, mill around the corner of Devilliers and Wylie... - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Crowd of men and women gathered in street for funeral of Charlie Williams, at Wylie Avenue and Devilliers Street, Hill District
